The paper discusses automatic methods for generating neural network architectures, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on neural architecture search (NAS) techniques, which are a subset of machine learning methods that involve searching for the optimal neural network architecture. This makes cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of NAS techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE), which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a solution to a failure mode in NAS techniques, which involves training the controller's hidden state with a memory buffer of previously sampled architectures. This solution involves a control system, which falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
